# 2026-03-05 (cont. 8 — all six status flags green)

Implemented all six status flags in `SetFlags` method. Full Execute pipeline working for byte reg-to-reg ADD.

## What Was Built

* Cpu.cs — `SetFlags(int result, ushort source, ushort destination, bool word)` computes all 6 status flags:
  - CF: `result > 0xFF` (byte) / `result > 0xFFFF` (word)
  - AF: `(source & 0x0F) + (destination & 0x0F) > 0x0F` (nibble carry, ADD-only for now)
  - SF: `(result & 0x80) != 0` (byte) / `(result & 0x8000) != 0` (word)
  - ZF: `result == 0`
  - PF: `BitOperations.PopCount((uint)result & 0xFF) % 2 == 0` (low byte only, Intel legacy)
  - OF: same-sign operands, opposite-sign result (three sign bit checks)
* Cpu.cs — `Execute` stores result as `int` (wider than operands) to preserve carry info. Calls `SetFlags` before `SetRegisterValue` so original operand values are available for AF/OF.
* CpuTests.cs — 7 tests total: GetRegisterValue, SetRegisterValue, plus 5 Execute tests each targeting a specific flag boundary (PF, AF, ZF, SF, OF).
* TestHarness.cs — null-forgiving operator on all Initial register accesses, killing 28 CS8629 warnings.

## Key Learnings

+ Flag test values are chosen at boundaries: `0x0F + 0x01` (nibble overflow), `0x7F + 0x01` (sign flip), `0x80 + 0x01` (stay negative), `0x00 + 0x00` (zero).
+ `int` result type is critical — truncating to `ushort` before flag checking loses carry info.
+ `SetFlags` must run before `SetRegisterValue` or destination reads get stale values.
+ Operator precedence: `&` binds looser than `+`. Always parenthesize masks: `(source & 0x0F) + (destination & 0x0F)`.
+ PF only checks low byte even on word ops — 8080 backward compatibility.

## Open

? AF formula is ADD-only. SUB needs borrow logic — XOR trick `(source ^ destination ^ result) & 0x10` handles both. Defer until SUB test demands it.
? CF test in isolation not yet written (`0xFF + 0x01`).
? Roslyn LSP code action keeps inlining `new Cpu()` on test variables — destructive, need to disable or suppress diagnostic.
? `[Theory]`/`[MemberData]` for Opcode00Tests still pending.

